log_trap is an extremely simple component that monitors the log
output of a child process and exits when it encounters a specific string.

This is useful when multiple children must be started in a scenario but the
entire scenario should exit when a single child meets a specific condition.


Configuration
-------------

! <start name="log_trap">
! 	<resource name="RAM" quantum="1G"/>
! 	<config pattern="--- test successful ---">
! 		<start name="init">
! 			<config>
! 				<parent-provides>
! 				...
! 			</config>
!		</start>
! 	</config>
! <start>